t3007.text: Trace chemicals in the alcohol, such as methanol, will evaporate quickly and will avoid toxicity issues. Other additives which are designed to make alcohol abuse by ingestion unpleasant in an irreversible way, eg. bitterants, colour, are ok for skin contact.

t3008.text: Note Well: don’t use methylated spirits straight as it will dry and damage your hands with repeated use. The aloe Vera is very important as it moisturises hands and counters some of the damaging effects of the alcohol.

t3009.text: The aloe Vera, I grow myself and just scraped into my recycled shampoo pump pack. For the pure alcohol, I researched methylated spirits and found that the current additives to denature(make metho unfit for drinking) are the ones also used in hand sanitizer.

t3010.text: I’ve been researching the viability and validity of making my own hand sanitizer. I can report success, safety, effectiveness, value for money, and avoiding items in short supply. The recipe is 3 parts aloe Vera, 7 parts pure alcohol, and a couple of drops of aftershave.
